| Step | Layer                         | What Happens                                       | Real-Time Example                        |
| ---- | ----------------------------- | -------------------------------------------------- | ---------------------------------------- |
| 1    | Input Image                   | Original image enters CNN                          | Upload a cat image                       |
| 2    | First Convolution Layer       | Detects simple features like edges and lines       | Finds cat ear edges                      |
| 3    | Max Pooling                   | Reduces image size while keeping important details | Keeps important ear patterns             |
| 4    | Second Convolution Layer      | Detects more complex patterns                      | Detects eyes and fur texture             |
| 5    | Average Pooling               | Further reduces dimensions                         | Keeps main facial structure              |
| 6    | Third Convolution Layer       | Learns high-level object features                  | Understands “this looks like a cat face” |
| 7    | Fully Connected / Dense Layer | Combines all learned features                      | Compares cat vs dog patterns             |
| 8    | Hidden Dense Layer            | Final decision-making process                      | Calculates probability                   |
| 9    | Output Layer                  | Gives final prediction                             | “Cat = 98%”                              |


